# forms.rules.md

### A. Purpose
Standardize all form design, behavior, and validation using Syncfusion UI Kit — Material-3 Theme components exclusively.

### B. Rules

**Structure:**
- All forms use Syncfusion's `FormValidator` for validation logic.
- Simple forms (≤ 6 fields): single column layout.
- Medium forms (7–15 fields): two-column layout using 6/6 grid split.
- Complex forms (> 15 fields or multi-domain): use `SfStepper` for multi-step progression.
- Group related fields under labeled sections with a divider and H4 heading.
- Section spacing: 32px between groups. Field spacing: 16px between fields.

**Syncfusion Component Per Field Type:**
- Short text → `SfTextBox`
- Long text → `SfTextBox` (multiline prop)
- Number → `SfNumericTextBox`
- Password → `SfTextBox` (type: password)
- Formatted input (phone, ID, IBAN) → `SfMaskedTextBox`
- Single select ≤ 5 options → `SfRadioButton`
- Single select long list → `SfDropDownList`
- Single select with search → `SfComboBox`
- Multi-select → `SfMultiSelect`
- Multi-select inline compact → `SfChip` / `SfChipList`
- Boolean setting → `SfSwitch`
- Agree/acknowledge → `SfCheckBox`
- Date → `SfDatePicker`
- Date range → `SfDateRangePicker`
- Date + time → `SfDateTimePicker`
- Time only → `SfTimePicker`
- File → `SfUploader`
- Color → `SfColorPicker`
- OTP → `SfOtpInput`
- Signature → `SfSignature`
- Rating → `SfRating`
- Range value → `SfSlider`

**Label and Helper Rules:**
- Every field MUST have a visible label — no placeholder-only fields.
- Labels appear ABOVE the field (RTL-safe).
- Required fields marked with `*` after label text.
- Helper text below field: Caption style (12px, `--color-sf-on-surface-variant`).
- Error text replaces helper text using `--color-sf-error`.
- Character count shown below `SfTextBox` multiline when limit exists.

**Validation:**
- Use `FormValidator` — validate on blur and on submit.
- Errors appear inline below the field via Syncfusion's built-in error display.
- Error message format: "What is wrong. How to fix it."
- Multi-field errors also shown in `SfMessage` (error variant) at top of form on submit.
- Disable submit button during submission — show `SfSpinner` inside `SfButton`.
- On success: show `SfToast` (success variant).

**Progressive Disclosure:**
- Advanced fields hidden behind `SfAccordion` toggle.
- Conditional fields use show/hide with smooth transition.
- Multi-stage flows always use `SfStepper` — never multiple pages.

**RTL:**
- All Syncfusion form components respect `enableRtl(true)` automatically.
- Labels, helper text, and error messages align right in RTL.
- Do not manually set `direction: rtl` on individual components.

**Accessibility:**
- Syncfusion components include ARIA by default — do not remove.
- `SfTextBox`, `SfDropDownList`, etc. all support `aria-label` and `aria-describedby` props.
- Focus order follows RTL reading direction automatically when `enableRtl` is active.

### C. Do / Don't

**Do:**
- ✅ Use `SfStepper` for forms with > 15 fields or distinct logical stages.
- ✅ Use `FormValidator` for all validation — never manual validation logic.
- ✅ Use the correct Syncfusion input component per data type.
- ✅ Group related fields with section headers and 32px spacing.
- ✅ Disable submit during processing with `SfSpinner` inside `SfButton`.

**Don't:**
- ❌ Do not use `<input>` or `<select>` HTML directly — always use Syncfusion components.
- ❌ Do not use placeholder text as a substitute for labels.
- ❌ Do not validate on every keystroke.
- ❌ Do not use `SfTextBox` for date input — always `SfDatePicker`.
- ❌ Do not mix `SfCheckBox` and `SfSwitch` for the same type of boolean decision.
- ❌ Do not build custom dropdowns — use `SfDropDownList` or `SfComboBox`.

### D. MCP Usage Guidance
- When generating a form, identify field count/type → select single/two-column/stepper layout.
- Auto-map each field to its Syncfusion Material-3 component.
- Auto-apply: label above field, 16px between fields, 32px between sections, `*` for required.
- Always generate validation state variants: default, error, success, disabled.
- For Stepper forms, generate each step as a discrete section with Back/Next/Submit `SfButton` controls.
- Reference Syncfusion Figma Kit layer names when mapping from Figma frames to code components.
